{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/42547", "repository_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/42547/labels{/name}", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/42547/comments", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/42547/events", "html_url": "https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/42547", "id": 234624597, "node_id": "MDU6SXNzdWUyMzQ2MjQ1OTc=", "number": 42547, "title": "Allow packed enums", "user": {"login": "main--", "id": 754850, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjc1NDg1MA==", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/754850?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/main--", "html_url": "https://github.com/main--", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/main--/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/main--/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/main--/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/main--/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/main--/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/main--/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/main--/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/main--/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/main--/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "labels": [], "state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 5, "created_at": "2017-06-08T19:00:13Z", "updated_at": "2017-06-23T18:12:35Z", "closed_at": "2017-06-23T03:53:30Z", "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "```rust\r\nuse std::mem::size_of;\r\n\r\nstruct Foo {\r\n    id: u32,\r\n    tag: u32,\r\n    inner: FooInner,\r\n}\r\n\r\nunion FooInner {\r\n    a: u64,\r\n    b: u64,\r\n}\r\n\r\n#[repr(packed)]\r\nstruct Bar {\r\n    id: u32,\r\n    inner: BarInner,\r\n}\r\n\r\n#[repr(u32)]\r\nenum BarInner {\r\n    A(u64),\r\n    B(u64),\r\n}\r\n\r\nfn main() {\r\n    println!(\"{} vs {}\", size_of::<Foo>(), size_of::<Bar>());\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nBecause its members have 8-byte alignment, the enum always insists on inserting up to 7 bytes of padding, depending on the discriminant size (4 here). This is usually correct - except in cases like this one where I just **know** that this enum will always be inside a wrapper that ensures correct alignment. Without the `packed` attribute, `Bar` now has `id` followed by 4 padding bytes, then the enum discriminant and *another 4 bytes of padding* even though all the data would neatly fit into 16 bytes, as `Foo` shows.\r\n\r\nThe `#[repr(packed)]` on `Bar` successfully gets rid of the first padding but there's no way to do the same for the second one as packed enums aren't allowed.", "closed_by": {"login": "Mark-Simulacrum", "id": 5047365, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjUwNDczNjU=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/5047365?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/Mark-Simulacrum", "html_url": "https://github.com/Mark-Simulacrum", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Mark-Simulacrum/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Mark-Simulacrum/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Mark-Simulacrum/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Mark-Simulacrum/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Mark-Simulacrum/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Mark-Simulacrum/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Mark-Simulacrum/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Mark-Simulacrum/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Mark-Simulacrum/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/